{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04511/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04511"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:45:11"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["plan américain"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["high"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, pan"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man lays in bed, pained."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04511/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04511","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04511/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04511"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04511/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04511/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04511/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04511/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04511/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04511/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04511/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04511/canvas/1/cb578bdf-8965-4123-a9bc-febe6518dce0","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:17:01.291Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Lying in bed, Reynolds resembles both a corpse and, as Alma suggests, a sick child. He is associated at once with the “dead” House of Woodcock and with childhood.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04511/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:569.8715230664858,468.63615162822254,634.6442503392133,506.35303595658087"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04511/canvas/1/6ae5eb2c-108c-4f06-bfb8-a213a9239f60","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:17:34.505Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>This pattern of intense work followed by a period of recuperation was drawn from the life of Cristóbal Balenciaga: “The tradesman in him had to be pleased and the artist gratified, although he was incapable of satisfaction, always believing he could do better. The reaction of the man himself remains opaque, one reason being that he was so rarely around. He would prepare the collections in Paris, and then when they were over go to Spain to recuperate and to oversee his Spanish houses” (Blume, <em>The Master of Us All</em>, 128).</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04511/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:19.003158308906123,24.47295648922001,223.20641112618733,204.01755427408415"}}}]}]}]}